<br>
2) The Elder that receives the /Tell or responds to the message will tack charge of this recruitment and be the lead Elder for this cub.<br>
<br>
3) The Elder will post the Cubs name on a thread on the Drinal Cubs message board.<br>
<br>
4) All wolves should look at the Cubs message board.  If some one sees a cub that they feel should not be a member they need to post under this cubs thread their feelings and why. (The lead Elder must investigate this and choose to drop or continue the process.  The Perspective Cub should be informed that they where denied.<br>
<br>
5) The Lead Elder will Interview* the person via /Tell or Email to see if they like the person (see below)<br>
<br>
6) Then the Lead Elder will have a second Elder interview the person.<br>
<br>
7) Once both Elders agree a mentor will be assigned and the cub tagged (One character only).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Mentoring** will take roughly one month (See below).  <br>
<br>
9) At the completion of mentoring the Elder will assign a quest.<br>
<br>
10) At the completion of the quest the Cub will be promoted to pup.<br>
<br>
Note: At anytime during the thirty day trial period the cub may be detagged for repeated poor behavior by an Elder.  The Elder should give explination.<br>
<br>
*Interviews – These have not time specification it is simply saying hello and finding out why this person wants to be a wolf and what it means to be one.  Use your own judgement.  I would like every one to take this a bit seriously and at least talk to the person for at least 15-min.<br>
<br>
**Mentoring – Mentoring will no longer require actually running with the cub.  The cub will be tagged.  The mentor’s job will be to be a “Big Brother/Sister”.  Speak with the Cub once assigned.  Get to know them and be available if they have questions.  Though it is not required I would like to see Mentors and Cubs meet Avatar to Avatar at lease once in the month long period.  Some examples of the things the mentor should help the cub with are the Message board and Web page.  Making sure they know where they are and how to use them.  They should explain to the about the Call of the Wild (Our in zone Howl) and how to answer it.    Helping with their Cub quest is allowed and even recommended.  Also if you get to know the person you could even recommend a quest to the Elder.  <br>
<br>
This form of mentoring will take less game time on behalf of the mentor and should insure a closer nit guild.  Mentors really will be mentors.  If you have any problems or questions about mentoring at any time contact an Elder or me.  Mentors must be wolf rank or above.<br>
