<br>
HOWEVER,<br>
<br>
I think the line-of-sight mentoring is very important, it keeps the quality of members high, so the guild will get a reputation for having high quality members, which will improve our chances of being invited into parties and the like.<br>
<br>
It will also make like-minded (e.g. competent and polite) players want to join us.<br>
<br>
If we invite careless or rude players then that will stack against the guild and will bring the guild down to a &quot;oh, they invite anyone&quot; level. Playing big brother/sister at a distance will not give us any warning that this may happen.<br>
<br>
Reputation is hard to gain but easy to lose.<br>
<br>
I'm proud to be an aegis wolf. Don't lose that. <p>--
